commit.message:
Fix cancel handling in python 3.8/3.9. (#175)

We need to explicitely catch asyncio.CancelledError as of python3.8
as it now inherits from BaseException instead of Exception.

As of python3.9 a message can be passed to Future.cancel(), add an
optional kwarg for that and pass it to Future.cancel() when available.

Co-authored-by: Omer Akram <om26er@gmail.com>

Fix cancel handling in python 3.8/3.9. (#175)

We need to explicitely catch asyncio.CancelledError as of python3.8
as it now inherits from BaseException instead of Exception.

As of python3.9 a message can be passed to Future.cancel(), add an
optional kwarg for that and pass it to Future.cancel() when available.

Co-authored-by: Omer Akram <om26er@gmail.com>
